The paper deals with the synthesis of optimal strategies in Markov decision processes (MDPs) with large state spaces. This topic is relevant to several subfields of computer science, including logic (cs.LO), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data structures (cs.DS), programming languages (cs.PL), and systems and control (cs.SY). However, given that the paper focuses on the design of efficient algorithms for MDPs, we believe that cs.LO and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.DS, cs.PL, and cs.SY.
